1 (h) The State Fire Marshal shall not, so long as the revocation or suspension remains in
2 effect, issue any new license or permit for the establishment of any new firm, business, or
3 corporation of any individual or applicant that has or will have the same or similar management,
4 ownership, control, employees, permittees, or licensees or will use the same or a similar name as
5 the revoked or suspended firm, business, corporation, individual, or applicant.
6 "§ 58-82C-11. Grounds for denial, suspension, probation, revocation, or nonrenewal of
7 licenses or permits.
8 The State Fire Marshal may deny, suspend, place on probation, revoke, or refuse to renew
9 any license or permit under this Article, in accordance with the provisions of Article 3A of
10 Chapter 150B of the General Statutes, for any one or more of the following reasons:
11 (1) Performing any action for which a license or permit is required under this
12 Article without having first obtained such license or permit.
13 (2) Improperly installing, recharging, repairing, servicing, inspecting, or testing a
14 portable fire extinguisher or fire suppression system.
15 (3) Rendering inoperative a portable fire extinguisher or pre-engineered or
16 engineered fire suppression system covered by this Article, except during the
17 time the extinguisher or system is being inspected, recharged, repaired,
18 serviced, or tested or except pursuant to court order.
19 (4) Material misstatement, misrepresentation, or fraud in obtaining a license or
20 permit under this Article.
21 (5) Failing to provide proof of or maintain the minimum comprehensive liability
22 insurance coverage as set forth in G.S. 58-82C-5.
23 (6) Failing to notify the State Fire Marshal, in writing, within 30 days after a
24 change of any information required on applications under G.S. 58-82C-8.
25 (7) Cheating on an examination for a license or permit, if an examination is
26 required by the State Fire Marshal pursuant to this Article.
27 (8) Having any professional license denied, suspended, or revoked in this State or
28 any other jurisdiction for causes substantially similar to those listed in this
29 subsection.
30 (9) Failing or refusing to comply with a cease and desist order or any other notice
31 or order to correct a violation related to conduct governed by this Article.
32 (10) Retaining an officer, director, stockholder, owner, or individual who has a
33 direct or indirect interest that has had his or her license or permit suspended
34 or revoked under this Article.
35 (11) Serving or previously serving as an officer, director, stockholder, or owner of
36 a firm, business, or corporation whose license or permit has been suspended
37 or revoked under this Article, or who has or had a direct or indirect interest in
38 a firm, business, or corporation whose license or permit has been suspended
39 or revoked under this Article.
40 (12) While holding a permit or license, using a license or permit or license number
41 or permit number other than his or her own valid license or permit or license
42 number or permit number.
43 (13) Using credentials, methods, means, or practices to impersonate a
44 representative of the State Fire Marshal or any local fire chief, fire marshal,
45 or other fire authority having jurisdiction.
46 (14) Any cause for which the issuance of the license or permit could have been
47 denied had it been known to the State Fire Marshal at the time of issuance.
48 (15) Failing to obtain, retain, or maintain one or more of the qualifications for a
49 license or permit required by this Article.
50 (16) Knowingly aiding or abetting others to evade or violate the provisions of this
51 Article.
